1263
00:40:00,740 --> 00:40:02,270
I'll do it. You just sit still.

1264
00:40:02,270 --> 00:40:03,810
No, it's not that. This is...

1265
00:40:03,840 --> 00:40:05,640
- It's cooked, right? - You can eat this.

1266
00:40:05,780 --> 00:40:06,880
Thank you for the meal.

1267
00:40:06,910 --> 00:40:09,010
- Shall we add some perilla leaves? - I hate adding perilla leaves.

1268
00:40:11,310 --> 00:40:13,250
This sauce! Hurry up and try it with the sauce, Ji Hyo.

1269
00:40:13,380 --> 00:40:14,620
Shall we add some perilla leaves?

1270
00:40:14,780 --> 00:40:16,990
- No! No perilla leaves. - Why?

1271
00:40:16,990 --> 00:40:18,790
I hate adding perilla leaves.

1272
00:40:20,490 --> 00:40:21,690
Didn't you guys add perilla leaves?

1273
00:40:21,690 --> 00:40:22,790
We didn't.

1274
00:40:24,530 --> 00:40:26,360
But it's only good if you add perilla leaves.

1275
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:30,270
It's so good!

1276
00:40:30,270 --> 00:40:31,830
The fried rice is... My goodness.

1277
00:40:31,830 --> 00:40:32,940
Is it normally served like this?

1278
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:34,570
- That's ours. - I mean,

1279
00:40:34,570 --> 00:40:35,700
I thought you were here last week.

1280
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:36,940
Seok Jin, this is ours.

1281
00:40:37,810 --> 00:40:39,110
Why are you eating our food?

1282
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:40,980
- You find me difficult. - Well...

1283
00:40:40,980 --> 00:40:42,680
I'm his senior, so he finds me difficult.

1284
00:40:42,680 --> 00:40:43,880
- It's my master's. - Right.

1285
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:46,050
- Wait, but this is ours. - I can't touch him.

1286
00:40:46,650 --> 00:40:47,920
- It's good, right? - Yes.

1287
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:49,820
- I barely stay alive. - I see.

1288
00:40:52,590 --> 00:40:54,060
We can eat it once it boils.

1289
00:40:54,390 --> 00:40:55,460
So, can we eat it now?

1290
00:40:56,330 --> 00:40:58,230
Try a noodle to see if it's done.

1291
00:41:00,060 --> 00:41:01,100
It's perfect.

1292
00:41:01,100 --> 00:41:02,230
This is good.

1293
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:08,300
It's really good.

1294
00:41:12,310 --> 00:41:13,410
- By the way... - Hey, to be honest...

1295
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:17,950
For someone like Jae Seok, among your Gen Z friends,

1296
00:41:17,950 --> 00:41:20,080
- how handsome is he seen as? - Yes?

1297
00:41:20,080 --> 00:41:22,120
But really, Jae Seok is...

1298
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:23,790
- He really has that. - What?

1299
00:41:24,990 --> 00:41:26,560
He has good looks that were created by his fame.

1300
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:29,590
What if he didn't have fame?

1301
00:41:29,790 --> 00:41:31,290
There's no way for him not to have fame.

1302
00:41:31,290 --> 00:41:32,600
- You know, - Yes?

1303
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:34,430
when I went on a group blind date with Sookmyung University students,

1304
00:41:34,430 --> 00:41:35,760
- I was... - Why did you do such a thing?

1305
00:41:35,760 --> 00:41:37,230
I was the most popular guy.

1306
00:41:37,230 --> 00:41:39,300
- Hey, who were the other guys? - I know.

1307
00:41:39,300 --> 00:41:40,540
- The other guys... - My friends...

1308
00:41:40,540 --> 00:41:41,770
- were a total mess. - Hey.

1309
00:41:41,940 --> 00:41:43,870
I only chose friends like that.

1310
00:41:43,970 --> 00:41:46,240
- When I was in 11th grade, - Yes?

1311
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:47,680
- we had... - What happened?

1312
00:41:47,680 --> 00:41:49,810
We had a group date where the girls chose our belongings.

1313
00:41:50,010 --> 00:41:51,650
All three girls chose me.

1314
00:41:51,650 --> 00:41:52,950
As the person they wish who would leave?

1315
00:41:53,580 --> 00:41:54,780
- The person they liked. - Still, Seok Jin...

1316
00:41:54,780 --> 00:41:56,220
Don't lie.

1317
00:41:56,220 --> 00:41:58,550
- I hung out a lot with these guys. - Yes.

1318
00:41:58,820 --> 00:42:00,190
He just...

1319
00:42:00,190 --> 00:42:01,490
Seriously, I thought he was a cicada.

1320
00:42:01,490 --> 00:42:02,760
He was stuck to his date...

1321
00:42:03,130 --> 00:42:04,960
and talking her ear off.

1322
00:42:06,530 --> 00:42:07,600
Okay, now,

1323
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:09,730
- you're done eating, right? - Yes.

1324
00:42:09,970 --> 00:42:12,600
From now on, you will each split up.

1325
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:16,270
We'll give you 20 minutes to hide your cell phones.

1326
00:42:16,640 --> 00:42:17,740
Here?

1327
00:42:18,070 --> 00:42:20,510
You may only hide your cell phones...

1328
00:42:20,510 --> 00:42:23,710
in a 1km radius from Dosan Park.

1329
00:42:24,210 --> 00:42:26,120
Once you hide your cell phone,

1330
00:42:26,120 --> 00:42:28,550
you may start searching for other people's phones.

1331
00:42:28,550 --> 00:42:30,220
- A 1km radius from Dosan Park. - My gosh.

1332
00:42:30,220 --> 00:42:33,190
You may feel lost about where to find...

1333
00:42:33,190 --> 00:42:34,490
- the other members' phones. - Right.

1334
00:42:34,490 --> 00:42:37,060
- You can get location hints. - Yes.

1335
00:42:37,060 --> 00:42:39,600
Those hints will be available at Dosan Park.

1336
00:42:39,730 --> 00:42:41,800
You'll see it's written in a special way.

1337
00:42:41,800 --> 00:42:43,170
- Once you see it... - In Dosan Park?

1338
00:42:43,170 --> 00:42:44,170
- Yes. - I see.

1339
00:42:44,170 --> 00:42:46,570
You'll be able to receive a hint.

1340
00:42:47,470 --> 00:42:50,310
The game will be over when there's only one player remaining.

1341
00:42:51,010 --> 00:42:54,110
Remember where we filmed the opening today?

1342
00:42:54,110 --> 00:42:56,210
- Would that be around 1km? - Yes.

1343
00:42:57,110 --> 00:42:58,510
Are you planning to hide it at home?

1344
00:42:58,650 --> 00:43:00,220
- Then... - The boxing gym is right there.

1345
00:43:00,220 --> 00:43:02,420
- I see. - I could hide it at the boxing gym.

1346
00:43:02,920 --> 00:43:04,590
Should you be brainstorming together?

1347
00:43:04,890 --> 00:43:06,120
We're a team.

1348
00:43:06,120 --> 00:43:07,390
- We're one team. - Right.

1349
00:43:07,620 --> 00:43:08,820
We're a team.

1350
00:43:08,820 --> 00:43:10,160
- We're one team. - Right.

1351
00:43:11,130 --> 00:43:12,900
I trust the boy at Antenna.

1352
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:15,060
I trust the boy at Antenna.

1353
00:43:15,600 --> 00:43:18,570
I'm not thinking of him as someone signed with Antenna.

1354
00:43:18,570 --> 00:43:20,370
- He's part of the Nevis Swing Clan. - Nevis!

1355
00:43:20,370 --> 00:43:22,100
- That's right. - This is his chance...

1356
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:24,010
to come back to us.

1357
00:43:24,940 --> 00:43:27,180
Did you see his expression just now?

1358
00:43:27,180 --> 00:43:28,580
- I mean it. - You're right.

1359
00:43:28,840 --> 00:43:31,210
- I'm with Haha. - We're...

1360
00:43:31,350 --> 00:43:33,020
- I want to give you a chance. - Right.

1361
00:43:33,320 --> 00:43:34,550
Let's remember the moments we shared...

1362
00:43:34,620 --> 00:43:35,750
riding the Nevis Swing.

1363
00:43:35,750 --> 00:43:38,750
To be honest, I've been wanting to set you straight.

1364
00:43:39,420 --> 00:43:40,660
On your own?

1365
00:43:41,260 --> 00:43:42,760
With Jong Kook, you brat.

1366
00:43:45,630 --> 00:43:47,130
- I'll set you straight. - Sure.

1367
00:43:47,160 --> 00:43:49,200
You can go ahead and hide your phones.

1368
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:51,270
- Off we go! - Let's go!

1369
00:43:51,670 --> 00:43:53,070
- Seok Sam, quickly. - Sure.

1370
00:43:53,070 --> 00:43:55,100
- Move it. - Okay.

1371
00:43:55,640 --> 00:43:56,710
I'm coming!

1372
00:43:57,140 --> 00:43:59,340
I'm never the one who serves someone else.

1373
00:43:59,680 --> 00:44:00,940
Unbelievable.

1374
00:44:01,540 --> 00:44:03,750
I don't want to dress up as Ddochi or an "Avatar" character.

1375
00:44:03,950 --> 00:44:05,450
I want to be a princess.

1376
00:44:06,250 --> 00:44:08,120
I'll hide it where they'll never find it.

1377
00:44:08,250 --> 00:44:09,850
How far away is a kilometer?

1378
00:44:10,220 --> 00:44:12,120
Where can I hide this?

1379
00:44:12,120 --> 00:44:13,590
I need to win.

1380
00:44:14,190 --> 00:44:16,660
- Goodness. - Where should I hide this?

1381
00:44:16,730 --> 00:44:17,760
What?

1382
00:44:19,930 --> 00:44:21,700
Hiding it is key,

1383
00:44:24,100 --> 00:44:25,670
so why not let me hold onto it?

1384
00:44:25,970 --> 00:44:27,840
- I could... - That's a bad idea.

1385
00:44:28,340 --> 00:44:29,940
- You'll go there and... - They'll never guess it.

1386
00:44:29,940 --> 00:44:32,570
- They'll never guess it. - You'll go there and...

1387
00:44:32,570 --> 00:44:34,540
You'll go to the others and hand it over.

1388
00:44:35,010 --> 00:44:37,210
- I wouldn't. - You'll bargain with it.

1389
00:44:37,210 --> 00:44:38,380
- I'm not that kind of person. - You'll...

1390
00:44:38,680 --> 00:44:41,020
- I'm not that kind of person. - Forget it.

1391
00:44:41,620 --> 00:44:42,620
Just let me have it.

1392
00:44:42,620 --> 00:44:44,450
- All I have to do is stay... - Don't.

1393
00:44:44,450 --> 00:44:45,950
- within a kilometer of you. - Forget it.

1394
00:44:45,950 --> 00:44:47,960
- I'll stay in Dosan Park. - I know how you are.

1395
00:44:48,090 --> 00:44:49,120
- What do you mean? - I know you.

1396
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:50,530
Why would you think of me like that?

1397
00:44:50,530 --> 00:44:52,130
Why else?

1398
00:44:52,460 --> 00:44:54,100
You've got to be kidding me.

1399
00:44:54,360 --> 00:44:57,730
How about a shoe locker at a fitness center?

1400
00:44:58,130 --> 00:45:00,070
Let's put in inside one of the shoes.

1401
00:45:00,370 --> 00:45:01,670
- Clever, right? - Everyone...

1402
00:45:01,900 --> 00:45:03,740
will be thinking that.

1403
00:45:04,110 --> 00:45:06,380
Then what's a place no one would think of?

1404
00:45:06,610 --> 00:45:07,680
Just where?

1405
00:45:08,010 --> 00:45:10,050
I should really go to my boxing gym.

1406
00:45:10,210 --> 00:45:11,250
That's 8km away.

1407
00:45:11,250 --> 00:45:12,750
Gosh, is it that far away?

1408
00:45:13,550 --> 00:45:15,050
I can't go there then.

1409
00:45:15,550 --> 00:45:17,220
That's too far away.

1410
00:45:18,220 --> 00:45:19,690
What would be a good place nearby?

1411
00:45:19,690 --> 00:45:21,660
Even the fitness center would be far away.

1412
00:45:24,730 --> 00:45:27,130
Maybe I should hide it in Tae Hyun's house.

1413
00:45:30,330 --> 00:45:32,370
There's a good chance he's home. I should call him.

1414
00:45:36,470 --> 00:45:37,740
- Hey. - Where are you?

1415
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:39,680
I'm working out.

1416
00:45:42,340 --> 00:45:43,680
You're working out?

1417
00:45:44,750 --> 00:45:46,720
I always work out at lunchtime.

1418
00:45:48,050 --> 00:45:50,420
I'm filming Running Man right now.

1419
00:45:51,220 --> 00:45:54,160
- Sure. - I need to hide something...

1420
00:45:54,160 --> 00:45:55,890
within a 1km radius of Dosan Park.

1421
00:45:56,190 --> 00:45:58,130
Are you saying you're coming over?

1422
00:45:58,130 --> 00:45:59,800
I was just about to shower.

1423
00:46:00,200 --> 00:46:01,500
You're going to shower?

1424
00:46:01,860 --> 00:46:04,530
Can't you recommend a good hiding place?

1425
00:46:05,570 --> 00:46:06,900
Hide it in my office.

1426
00:46:06,900 --> 00:46:09,070
Wait, yes. That place.

1427
00:46:09,540 --> 00:46:10,570
Are you sure?

1428
00:46:11,670 --> 00:46:13,880
- Of course. - Can people see your building?

1429
00:46:14,980 --> 00:46:16,380
There's nothing there anyway.

1430
00:46:17,380 --> 00:46:19,280
- It's just my office space. - Really?

1431
00:46:19,410 --> 00:46:21,520
Have you still not found tenants for the spaces?

1432
00:46:21,820 --> 00:46:24,020
Not yet. Why are you...

1433
00:46:24,390 --> 00:46:26,320
Why are you rubbing salt in the wound?

1434
00:46:26,320 --> 00:46:27,720
Once this airs on TV,

1435
00:46:27,720 --> 00:46:29,460
people might line up to rent the space.

1436
00:46:29,960 --> 00:46:32,430
I'll promote it for you.

1437
00:46:32,560 --> 00:46:35,630
I'll hide it in your office. That's a great idea.

1438
00:46:36,200 --> 00:46:38,870
- Sure. - This is incredible.

1439
00:46:40,200 --> 00:46:42,500
Aren't you curious about Tae Hyun's new building?

1440
00:46:42,500 --> 00:46:45,640
Many of the spaces haven't been leased yet.

1441
00:46:47,180 --> 00:46:48,180
Okay, let's go.

1442
00:46:48,180 --> 00:46:50,280
I've been to the building before, and it's nice.

1443
00:46:50,780 --> 00:46:52,610
I should hide it quickly and start looking.

1444
00:46:52,610 --> 00:46:54,280
- Right. - Where do I receive the hint?

1445
00:46:54,480 --> 00:46:56,220
- Hide it, then go to Dosan Park? - That's right.

1446
00:46:56,220 --> 00:46:57,290
Okay.

1447
00:46:58,220 --> 00:46:59,390
Haha's calling.

1448
00:46:59,790 --> 00:47:02,360
Hey, Haha. Go, Nevis Swing!

1449
00:47:02,460 --> 00:47:03,730
That's it. Go, Nevis Swing.

1450
00:47:03,730 --> 00:47:05,360
- Yes. - We're a united team now.

1451
00:47:05,360 --> 00:47:06,400
Of course.

1452
00:47:06,400 --> 00:47:09,630
One of the three of us has to win this game.

1453
00:47:09,770 --> 00:47:10,900
That's right. And...

1454
00:47:10,900 --> 00:47:13,400
You don't need a hint about where my phone is.

1455
00:47:13,400 --> 00:47:15,340
One of the three of us should become the winner.

1456
00:47:15,340 --> 00:47:17,340
Can't I tell you where mine is?

1457
00:47:17,340 --> 00:47:19,270
It'd be easier for me to be your minion.

1458
00:47:19,270 --> 00:47:20,310
That's an option.

1459
00:47:20,310 --> 00:47:22,740
Let's do that if things don't progress.

1460
00:47:22,740 --> 00:47:23,780
Okay.

1461
00:47:23,780 --> 00:47:26,220
For now, let's search for the other phones together.

1462
00:47:26,220 --> 00:47:27,250
Sounds good.

1463
00:47:27,250 --> 00:47:29,180
I'll be going to the Han River first.

1464
00:47:29,180 --> 00:47:30,220
Just know that.

1465
00:47:30,350 --> 00:47:31,390
Why are you going to the Han River?

1466
00:47:31,750 --> 00:47:32,960
That must be over a kilometer away.

1467
00:47:33,060 --> 00:47:34,960
No, it's right there.

1468
00:47:34,960 --> 00:47:36,660
The Han River is behind the Galleria Department Store.

1469
00:47:36,660 --> 00:47:39,330
Really? Well, I'm heading toward Dosan Park.

1470
00:47:39,700 --> 00:47:40,800
Okay.

1471
00:47:40,800 --> 00:47:41,960
- Got it, Haha. - Got it.

1472
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:43,470
- Go, team. - Of course.

1473
00:47:43,470 --> 00:47:45,130
- We're one. - Nevis!

1474
00:47:45,130 --> 00:47:46,970
Swing!

1475
00:47:48,970 --> 00:47:51,010
Let's stop by the Antenna building and head to the Han River.

1476
00:47:57,980 --> 00:47:59,510
This isn't a betrayal.

1477
00:48:00,080 --> 00:48:01,880
- I should aim to win. - Nevis!

1478
00:48:01,880 --> 00:48:02,880
- Swing! - Swing!

1479
00:48:02,950 --> 00:48:04,550
Isn't that the name of the game?

1480
00:48:04,550 --> 00:48:06,220
Not aiming to win...

1481
00:48:06,860 --> 00:48:09,590
means you don't understand the concept of this show.

1482
00:48:11,190 --> 00:48:12,490
As if I'd trust you.

1483
00:48:13,830 --> 00:48:15,200
Of course, I don't trust you.

1484
00:48:16,330 --> 00:48:18,030
The Han River's too obvious.

1485
00:48:18,600 --> 00:48:19,970
Can you take me to Rodeo Street?

1486
00:48:20,540 --> 00:48:21,740
- Rodeo Street? - Yes.

1487
00:48:24,340 --> 00:48:25,410
All right.

1488
00:48:27,140 --> 00:48:29,240
It's hard to say.

1489
00:48:30,810 --> 00:48:33,180
Somewhere obvious, but not too obvious.

1490
00:48:34,950 --> 00:48:37,390
The places I used to eat at are gone now.

1491
00:48:38,550 --> 00:48:39,590
No way.

1492
00:48:41,460 --> 00:48:44,130
I know that lady at the budaejjigae place.

1493
00:48:44,530 --> 00:48:45,930
That's my contingency plan.

1494
00:48:51,100 --> 00:48:52,570
Hey, it's someone I know.

1495
00:48:56,200 --> 00:48:57,340
- Sir. - Yes?

1496
00:48:57,340 --> 00:48:58,410
The owner must not be around.

1497
00:48:58,410 --> 00:48:59,940
He opened another shop somewhere else.

1498
00:48:59,940 --> 00:49:01,210
Really?

1499
00:49:02,610 --> 00:49:04,410
What a bummer.

1500
00:49:06,820 --> 00:49:09,150
How about... Did you know...

1501
00:49:09,250 --> 00:49:10,750
I'm good friends with the owner?

1502
00:49:10,890 --> 00:49:12,320
Yes, I heard about that.

1503
00:49:12,320 --> 00:49:14,290
- Back when I was lost, - Yes.

1504
00:49:14,420 --> 00:49:17,090
he straightened me out and sent me down the right path.

1505
00:49:17,190 --> 00:49:18,330
I heard you had a messy life.

1506
00:49:18,330 --> 00:49:19,590
A messy life?

1507
00:49:19,830 --> 00:49:21,500
I think that's what I heard.

1508
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:23,400
How can you say that on Running Man?

1509
00:49:23,400 --> 00:49:25,370
Sorry about that. He's my father.

1510
00:49:25,500 --> 00:49:26,840
- Is he your father? - Yes.

1511
00:49:26,840 --> 00:49:28,340
- Are you his son? - Yes.

1512
00:49:29,170 --> 00:49:30,210
It's great to meet you.

1513
00:49:30,610 --> 00:49:32,270
I used to act out.

1514
00:49:32,470 --> 00:49:35,380
I wouldn't say I had a messy life.

1515
00:49:35,380 --> 00:49:37,150
I was just hurting inside.

1516
00:49:37,980 --> 00:49:39,250
I was lost.

1517
00:49:39,410 --> 00:49:41,380
